d types, enums, API contracts\n- `@factory/frontend` - Shared frontend features\n- `@factory/droid-core` - AI agent core library\n\n### Client <-> daemon protocol\n\n- Shared JSON-RPC envelope/base protocol schemas live in `packages/common/src/shared/schemas.ts`\n- Daemon-side protocol schemas and exported types live under `packages/common/src/daemon/`\n- Client-side protocol schemas and exported types live under `packages/common/src/droid/`\n- `FACTORY_PROTOCOL_VERSION` lives in `packages/common/src/droid/schemas/constants.ts`\n- Protocol manifest CI enforcement lives in `apps/scripts/src/protocol-manifest/`; see `apps/scripts/src/protocol-manifest/README.md` before changing protocol schemas or protocol versioning rules\n\n---\n\n## Code Conventions\n\n- New API endpoints need types in `@factory/common/src/api/{service}/types.ts`\n- New UI components must use `@factory/core-ui` primitives (no raw `<div>`, `<button>`, `<input>`)\n- No hardcoded colors (use `colors.semantics`)\n- Extend existing abstractions rather than adding workaround logic in callers\n- Extract shared utilities instead of duplicating transformations across files\n- Don't remove safeguards (`.strict()`, assertions, validation) without documenting why\n- Search for existing patterns before creating new ones: `rg \"keyword\" --type ts`\n- Do not log user-generated content (session titles, message content, file contents, tool call params/results) in telemetry — CMEK-encrypted orgs expect this data to be opaque to the platform. See `packages/logging/src/metadata/types.ts` for the full policy.\n\n---\n\n## Testing\n\n- Do **not** run `npm run test`, `npm run typecheck`, or `npm run fix` unless explicitly requested\n- Prefer targeted checks where possible and ask before running repo-wide validators\n- For CLI unit tests, prefer `npm run test` / filtered `npm run test -- --filter=@factory/cli`. If you bypass npm scripts and invoke the runner directly, use `npx vitest`; CLI test helpers run under Vitest.\